# Nginx Configuration for FlowBlinq GEO

Your **Setup tab** has generated your specific Nginx config. Open it and look for the Nginx section — it will include your site's slug (derived from your domain).

## General Approach

For Nginx, you'll proxy FlowBlinq's files to your domain using a `location` block. Add this to your Nginx vhost config for `example.com`:

```nginx
location = /llms.txt {
    proxy_pass https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/YOUR-SLUG/llms.txt;
}

location = /llms-full.txt {
    proxy_pass https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/YOUR-SLUG/llms-full.txt;
}

location = /.well-known/ucp.json {
    proxy_pass https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/YOUR-SLUG/business.json;
}
```

Replace `YOUR-SLUG` with your site's slug (e.g., `example-com` for example.com — you'll see it in the Setup tab URLs).

## Steps

1. **Open the Setup tab** on your audit page — it shows your exact slug and config.
2. **Copy the Nginx block** from Setup.
3. **Paste into your Nginx config** (usually `/etc/nginx/sites-available/your-domain` or your main nginx.conf).
4. **Reload Nginx**: `sudo systemctl reload nginx`
5. **Verify**: Visit `https://example.com/llms.txt` — you should see your AI visibility file.

The Setup tab will also have the tracking pixel and robots.txt rules to add. Let me know if you need help with those! [1]
